que te guste. Pero si llegas al punto en que te encanta cmo te ves y cmo suenas cuando presentas, valdr la pena el tiempo invertido. Y tener esta habilidad te ahorrar tiempo para todas las futuras presentaciones en tu vida.</p>'),(44,2010,'en','New Update Features','The most complete course available on Product Management.','<p>Simply put, drip content is the practice of releasing your content to your members in parts. In other words, you don\'t release all the content to your members immediately.</p><p>Homework, or a homework assignment, is a set of tasks assigned to students by their teachers to be completed outside the classroom. Common homework assignments may include required reading, a writing or typing project, mathematical exercises to be completed, information to be reviewed before a test, or other skills to be practiced.</p><p><br></p><p>The effects of homework are debated. Generally speaking, homework does not improve academic performance among young children. Homework may improve academic skills among older students, especially lower-achieving students. However, homework also creates stress for students and parents and reduces the amount of time that students can spend in other activities.</p>'),(170,2022,'en','Installment and Secure Host','Installment payment is a popular method of paying for goods and services that allows customers to spread out the cost of a purchase over a period of time.','<p>Installment payment is a popular method of paying for goods and services that allows customers to spread out the cost of a purchase over a period of time. With installment payment, customers are able to pay for a product or service in smaller, more manageable amounts rather than having to pay the full amount upfront.</p><p><br></p><p>Installment payments are typically made on a monthly basis, and the amount of each payment is determined by the total cost of the purchase and the length of the repayment period. For example, if a customer purchases a product for $1,000 with a repayment period of 12 months, they would make 12 monthly payments of $83.33.</p><p><br></p><p>One of the benefits of installment payment is that it allows customers to make larger purchases that they may not be able to afford upfront. This can be particularly helpful for big-ticket items such as furniture, appliances, or electronics. By spreading out the cost of the purchase, customers can avoid having to pay a large sum of money all at once.</p><p><br></p><p>Another advantage of installment payment is that it can be a good option for customers who want to build their credit history. By making regular, on-time payments, customers can demonstrate their creditworthiness and potentially improve their credit score over time.</p><p><br></p><p>However, it\'s important to note that installment payment may not always be the most cost-effective option. Some installment plans may come with additional fees or higher interest rates than other payment methods. Customers should always read the terms and conditions carefully before agreeing to an installment payment plan to ensure they fully understand the costs involved.</p><p><br></p><p>Overall, installment payment is a flexible and convenient option that can make it easier for customers to make purchases they may not be able to afford upfront. Whether it\'s for a large purchase or to build credit, installment payment is a useful tool for many consumers.</p>'),(172,2024,'en','Product and Services Design forSME\'s',NULL,'<p>Nice Product</p>'),(175,2027,'en','e-Filing and Court Automation Processes','Understanding e-filing and court automation for efficient court administration','<p>This course provides legal professionals, court staff, and judges with an in-depth understanding of e-filing systems and court automation processes, which are transforming the modern judiciary. Participants will explore the benefits, challenges, and practical applications of transitioning from paper-based to electronic workflows. Topics include navigating e-filing platforms, submission requirements, document management, ensuring data security and privacy, and complying with jurisdiction-specific rules.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>The course will also cover broader court automation tools, such as case management systems, digital scheduling, virtual hearings, and integrating technology to enhance efficiency and access to justice. Attendees will engage in demonstrations, hands-on practice, and discussions on best practices to streamline their work in a digital court environment. This course is essential for professionals seeking to optimize their use of technology in the legal process and adapt to the evolving demands of court administration.</p>'),(176,2028,'en','Courtroom Management for Judges','Manage your courtroom effectively as a judge','<p>This course is designed to provide judges with the knowledge and tools necessary to effectively manage courtroom proceedings while maintaining fairness, efficiency, and decorum. Participants will explore strategies to handle a variety of courtroom scenarios, from managing case schedules and dealing with procedural disruptions to ensuring the rights of all parties are protected. Topics will include time management techniques, managing interactions with attorneys and self-represented litigants, handling difficult situations, integrating technology in the courtroom, and ensuring compliance with legal standards and ethical guidelines.</p><p>Through practical examples, case studies, and interactive discussions, judges will develop skills to foster a well-ordered and productive courtroom environment, minimizing delays and maximizing justice delivery. Whether new to the bench or seeking to refine existing skills, this course equips participants to navigate the complexities of courtroom management with confidence and professionalism.</p>'),(177,2029,'en','Judicial Ethics and Professionalism','Learn the principles of judicial ethics and professionalism essential for maintaining integrity, impartiality, and public trust in the Nigerian judiciary','<ul><li><p>Description<br>This course delves into the foundational principles of judicial ethics and professionalism, focusing on the Nigerian judiciary\'s expectations. Participants will explore topics such as integrity, impartiality, independence, and confidentiality. Practical case studies will highlight challenges in ethical decision-making and strategies for maintaining public trust. Whether you\'re a newly appointed judge, a senior judicial officer, or administrative staff, this course equips you with the tools to navigate ethical dilemmas confidently.</p></li></ul><p>Key Takeaways:</p><ul><li>Understanding the Code of Conduct for judicial officers in Nigeria.</li><li>Best practices for ensuring fairness and impartiality in decision-making.</li><li>Strategies to handle ethical dilemmas in the courtroom and beyond.</li><li>Strengthening public trust through transparency and accountability.</li></ul>'),(178,2030,'en','Avoiding Common Pitfalls in Legal Research and Writing','Learn how to manage case backlogs and implement efficient courtroom procedures to enhance justice delivery in Nigeria','<p>This course equips legal professionals with the skills and strategies to enhance the accuracy, clarity, and effectiveness of their legal research and writing. Participants will learn to identify and avoid common mistakes that can undermine legal arguments, compromise the credibility of written submissions, or result in procedural errors. Key topics include structuring persuasive legal arguments, avoiding over-reliance on weak precedents, proper citation practices, addressing ambiguities in statutes or case law, and proofreading techniques to eliminate errors.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Through hands-on exercises, real-world examples, and expert guidance, attendees will refine their ability to craft precise and compelling legal documents while ensuring thorough and reliable research practices. This course is ideal for attorneys, law clerks, and other legal professionals who want to strengthen their research and writing skills and deliver high-quality legal work that meets the demands of modern practice.</p>'),(179,2031,'en','Introduction to Social Justice and Gender Equality in Law','Social justice and Gender Equality','<p>This course introduces participants to the principles of social justice and gender equality as they intersect with the legal system. It explores how laws can both challenge and perpetuate inequalities, with a focus on the role of the judiciary, legal practitioners, and policymakers in advancing equity and justice. Key topics include the legal foundations of social justice, gender-based discrimination, human rights protections, access to justice for marginalized groups, and the impact of international conventions on domestic legal frameworks.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Participants will analyze case studies, landmark judgments, and contemporary legal reforms that address systemic inequities, including gender-based violence, workplace discrimination, property rights, and representation in decision-making. By the end of the course, attendees will understand the critical role of law in promoting social justice and gender equality, equipping them to advocate for and implement more inclusive legal practices. This course is ideal for students, legal professionals, and advocates seeking to address inequality through law and policy.</p>');
